### Combining all datasets (independent mass spec runs)
glob<-rbind(P53,P8,P45,ARY,AR13,D1)

dim(glob)
## [1] 1253   30
glob$Accession<-as.factor(as.character(glob$Accession)) #accession changed to factor


countrep<-ddply(glob,.(Accession),summarize,gene=length(X36))
genes6colony<-subset(countrep,countrep$gene==6)
genes6colony<-droplevels(genes6colony)

#### Combining dataset based on accessions that have representative colonies for all 6. 
Allcombined<-glob[glob$Accession %in% genes6colony$Accession,]

Statistics: ANOVA

Are there differences in parameters (Tm,slope,min) between ant species (3 reps each)

#ddply(paramfit,.(Accession,param),function(x){aov(Estimate~species,data=x)})


aovfit <- function(dat) {
  aov_fit <- summary(aov(Estimate~species, dat))[[1]][["Pr(>F)"]][1]
}
#summary(aov(Estimate~species,slope))[[1]][["Pr(>F)"]][1]

## Fitting anova
totalmod<-ddply(paramfit,.(Accession,param),aovfit)
# getting rows with low p-values
totalmod[which(totalmod$V1<0.05),]
